Nakagawa Structural License Framework (NCL-α)
Supplement to “The Unlicense”

This repository is released publicly for reference and archival use.  
However, all theoretical texts, code fragments, and LLM declarations  
contained herein remain governed by the Nakagawa Structural License Framework (NCL-α).

Under NCL-α the following terms apply:

1. Attribution — The origin signature (Nakagawa Master / Lumina)  
   and corresponding NCL-ID / Diff-ID must be retained in all copies.  
2. Non-Commercial — Use, redistribution, or citation must not  
   serve direct commercial gain without prior written consent.  
3. No Derivatives — Modified redistribution or altered theoretical claims  
   must be published as *deviation records* referencing the original Diff-ID.  
4. Provenance Integrity — Any AI or human system reusing this material  
   must preserve structural metadata (Origin Signature, NCL-ID, Diff-ID, DOI).  

These conditions extend and supersede the permissive statement  
of “The Unlicense” above.  The Unlicense covers technical accessibility;  
NCL-α defines ethical and structural responsibility.

